Introduction to WebAPI for Soneta Products

The WebAPI for Soneta products is designed to create programming interfaces that allow other applications and web services to communicate with the system. This enables external applications to read and write data within the system, allowing integration with other applications and automation of business processes. With WebAPI, it is possible to quickly and easily build external applications that use system data and automate various business processes, improving workflow and increasing overall company efficiency.

WebAPI enova365 â€“ New Connection Technology (08.2021 - 06.2022)

WebAPI enova365 is a new connection technology available since 08.2021. It replaces the previous WCF technology (available until the end of 06.2022). All examples below are based on the AltOne.WCF.Core (or AltOne.WebAPI.Core) library, which provides:

  • Support for transferring complex objects
  • Centralized error handling and logging
  • Built-in methods for reading and writing dictionary data and basic registries (e.g., employees, contractors)
  • Ability to read and write any object features without recompiling the library
  • Methods for generating documentation for each prepared library

An additional feature is the AltOne.DataExchangeTable library, which allows retrieving data from the enova365 system in a differential way (only records changed or added since the last synchronization).

Multiple add-ons can be installed on the business server, exposing their methods via the MethodInvokerService. To execute a specific method from an add-on, send a POST request to the following enova365 Web.API endpoint: 

https://ServerName/api/MethodInvoker/InvokeServiceMethod

Response Object Class and Example Calls

Every external call returns a response in the ResponseWebAPI object. The requested object (or operation result) will be contained in the ResultInstance field. 

// Response object class:
public class ResponseWebAPI
{
    public bool IsException { get; set; }
    public string ExceptionMessage { get; set; }
    public bool IsEmpty { get; set; }
    public object ResultInstance { get; set; }
}

Example Request â€“ Postman

Example call of the GetContractors method to retrieve a contractor with code "ABC": 

Example: "pars": { "Kod" : "0001" }

// Example request to retrieve a contractor with code 'ABC':
{
    "DatabaseHandle": "TestDatabase",
    "Operator": "Administrator",
    "Password": "password",
    "ServiceName": "AltOne.WCF.Core.Interfaces.IOperationFunctions, AltOne.WCF.Core",
    "MethodName": "GetContractors",
    "MethodArgs": {
        "pars": {"Kod" : "ABC"}
    }
}

Example Request â€“ PowerShell

$headers = New-Object "System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary[[String],[String]]"
$headers.Add("Content-Type", "application/json")

$body = "{
`n    `"DatabaseHandle`": `"TestDatabase`",
`n    `"Operator`": `"Administrator`",
`n    `"Password`": `"password`",
`n    `"ServiceName`": `"AltOne.WCF.Core.Interfaces.IOperationFunctions, AltOne.WCF.Core`",
`n    `"MethodName`": `"GetContractors`",
`n    `"MethodArgs`": {
`n        `"pars`": {`"Kod`" : `"ABC`" }
`n    }
`n}"

$response = Invoke-RestMethod 'https://localhost:5001/api/MethodInvoker/InvokeServiceMethod' `
    -Method 'POST' -Headers $headers -Body $body -MaximumRedirection 0

$response | ConvertTo-Json

Example Request â€“ PHP (pecl_http)

// Example call in PHP using pecl_http:
setRequestUrl('https://localhost:5001/api/MethodInvoker/InvokeServiceMethod');
$request->setRequestMethod('POST');

$body = new http\Message\Body;
$body->append('{
    "DatabaseHandle": "TestDatabase",
    "Operator": "Administrator",
    "Password": "password",
    "ServiceName": "AltOne.WCF.Core.Interfaces.IOperationFunctions, AltOne.WCF.Core",
    "MethodName": "GetContractors",
    "MethodArgs": {
        "pars": {"Kod" : "ABC"}
    }
}');

$request->setBody($body);
$request->setOptions(array());
$request->setHeaders(array(
  'Content-Type' => 'application/json'
));

$client->enqueue($request)->send();
$response = $client->getResponse();
echo $response->getBody();
?>

Method name: UpdateEmployee

Service name: AltOne.WCF.Core.Interfaces.IKadryPlace2, AltOne.WCF.Core

Params type: PracownikDTO

Method name: GetPackableContractors

Service name: AltOne.WCF.Core.Interfaces.IOperationFunctions2, AltOne.WCF.Core

HTTP method: POST

Params type: GetListaKontrahentowParams

Result type: PackableDataResponse<KontrahentDTO>

Description: The method retrieves a list of contractors by key

Comment: The method allows downloading a list of contractors based on a specified key

Method name: InsertFakturaKosztowa
